</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the following menus: DIAGNOSIS / ENHANCED OBD II / DATA LIST / MISFIRE / MISFIRE RPM and MISFIRE LOAD.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Read and note the MISFIRE RPM and MISFIRE LOAD (engine load) values.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>The MISFIRE RPM and MISFIRE LOAD values indicate the vehicle conditions under which the misfire occurred.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000XH301BX_10_0003" fin="false">NEXT</down>
